						<div class="postbody">Blaster Master would be a poor choice for a first project.<br /><br />I know what the hell I'm doing, and I wouldn't try it. Not that it couldn't be done, but the months of staring at disassembly, and testing and retesting would be a big enough disincentive, that I would skip it and do something else.<br /><br />A first project should be an NROM, non banking game with no scrolling. Like Donkey Kong, or Pac-man. Not that I would encourage anyone to hack any game. But, theoretically, it would be easier to modify a much simpler game.<br /><br />Edit -<br />This reminds me of the movie &quot;Son In Law&quot; where the grandfather is always whittling wood with a knife into horses and things, and Pauly Shore is like, can I whittle too? And then he grabs a piece of wood that is WAY too big to whittle.<br /><br />That.</div>

					
